Diagnosis.
FEMALE. Head with large coarse punctures. Mesosoma dark reddish brown, mesopleuron, metapleuron, antero-dorsal angle of lateral propodeal face and ventral half of posterior propodeal face blackish (
Fig. 2H
); thoracic dorsum with larger coarser punctures than on head, giving foveate-alveolate appearance (
Fig. 2D
); posterolateral propodeal margin distinctly dentate. T2 pale setal spots small, distance between them 1.43 × spot diameter (
Fig. 2D
); T3–4 with a pair of small lateral pale setal spots, distance between spots and that between spot and lateral margin of tergum approximately equal to spot diameter (
Fig. 2D
); pygidial plate irregularly rugose on anterior 1/2 and smooth posteriorly (
Fig. 12D
). MALE. Unknown.
